<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Brodder on 05-30-2000 10:05 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Sometimes you have to look at it situation by situation.
 In yours I'd have helped him kill regis and let him loot it. Then explained to him the error of his camping it alone, and the nature of several predatory farmer types. (INSERT your server's known KS EBAYER FARMERS ETC ETC here).

 I have a different way of dealing with things on bertoxxulous. It may get laughed off at first by the parties involved, or it will cause instant remorse and cries for forgiveness.

 1- AHEM We're engaging this spawn. (KS'rs froceed with the Kill) I then proceed to do the following.
  a- Target said person if they are ROLE or ANON and /guildstat take note of the guildnamed.
 b- Call off my group so as to not waste anymore mana or risk our health.
 c- /Log open
 d- Contact said guildleaders immediately if online...
 e- Screenshot of the conversation and persons actions in case said guildleaders want them (never been asked for em so far)
 f- tell teh person in open says. You have won this battle and stolen a kill from us. Yes there will be others. But you sir/madam have lost our respect and the chance of us ever helping you again. So shall our friends know this, so shall your name be entered into the book of grudges. And yes. All clerics shall know of your actions. Should you die, and yes it will one day happen. No succor shall be yours. No Heals, no rezzes, no aide in the recovery of your corpses. (sometimes, okay often, it's not this winded, but I'm on a roll here flow with it okay?)
 g- I then inform 3-5 of the online clerics I know or at random of said person's actions and to tell their friends.
 h- The word of a lvl 50 cleric carries allot of weight (YES I AM 50 NOW WOOOOOOHOOO, sorry had to slip that in there). If I am playing an alternate. I will tell the person who I am and that I remember. I watch.

 Thing is known KS'rs TRAINERS and general Aholes have ended up in groups with me in planar runs, dragon or FG raids and in Kunark dungeons. my first words to them...
  Do you remember me....I have a book and your name is in it...
  I pause and then I say, "Look how one with honor works, you are in my care now, I will not let you die on my watch. And if you do, I do too, and with honor and Valor" <<-- got to say that once only, but it was great fun.
 Thing is KS'rs and folks I swore I'd never group with again, if they have a choice demand that I group with their group on multi group raids.... I wonder if I should tell em I'm an Evo specialized cleric????
 Ever see what a stunned mob does when he's stunned for 10-12 seconds consecutively?
 They DIE...and die fast.  

 But back tot he topic (puts away his own horn)

 You can walk away from such a situation and hope for another chance at a later date. Aide  the youngster and hope he learns a lesson in compasion he can pass on to others in the virtual world.  Or lasley you can swear vengeance on a KS'r and make their life miserable on your server. Or you can compromise and do all three. Carrot, stick, the lil black book....all have their uses and place. Often others knowing you carry all three can stop a problem before ir starts.


Saint Brodder FoamyMugs
50 Cleric of Brell
Bertoxxulous server
Champion of Brell</TEXTAREA>
